[SN]TITLE[SN]
Guernsey Border Agency officer admits data offences

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A Guernsey Border Agency officer has admitted four offences relating to breaches of data protection law.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Matthew Walsh, 50, pleaded guilty to the charges in Guernsey's Magistrates Court.
Two of the charges relate to disclosing personal data and two to unauthorised access to data held in a computer belonging to the Home Department.
He is due to return to court on 19 November for sentencing.
